Exercise application to get post for one of X platform user: NASA, SpaceX, BoeingSpace

Use:
localhost:8080
    to enter simple console

Use:
GET http://localhost:8080/tweets/nasa
GET http://localhost:8080/tweets/spacex
GET http://localhost:8080/tweets/boeingspace
    to get last 5 tweets - and save new one's to database (mariadb).

Use:
GET http://localhost:8080/user/nasa
GET http://localhost:8080/user/spacex
GET http://localhost:8080/user/boeingspace
    to get short info about each user.

Use:
GET http://localhost:8080/db/tweets/nasa
GET http://localhost:8080/db/tweets/spacex
GET http://localhost:8080/db/tweets/boeingspace
    to display all tweets (as json) for specific user from database (mariadb)

Use:
POST http://localhost:8080/db/tweets/nasa
POST http://localhost:8080/db/tweets/spacex
POST http://localhost:8080/db/tweets/boeingspace
    to add a new tweet manually to database (mariadb)

In case of wrong user, dedicated error is risen ("User does not exist")